Secretary of State Antony Blinken, Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro N. Mayorkas, and White House Coordinator for Operation Allies Welcome Jack Markell led a roundtable discussion with CEOs to discuss the role of the private sector in welcoming and resettling Afghan allies. The meeting included leaders from various industries who have been engaged in the resettlement effort known as Operation Allies Welcome (OAW). During the meeting, Biden Administration officials provided updates on the resettlement efforts and participants shared their private sector initiatives to support the Afghan allies. The discussion focused on opportunities to provide resources and support for the successful resettlement of Afghans, including employment, housing, education, and healthcare. Operation Allies Welcome is the Biden Administration's initiative to provide a safe and dignified welcome to Afghan allies, and it aims to work with every American and organization that wants to help.